   <body>
      <p>It is important to understand how terms are used when working with the Adobe Sign Services application.</p>
      <p>
         <table>
            <tgroup cols="2">
               <colspec colname="col1"/>
               <colspec colname="col2"/>
               <thead>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Term</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Definition</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </thead>
               <tbody>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Agreement</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>The set of terms and conditions agreed between two or more parties. An agreement consists of structured Salesforce data and stored language dynamically generated into a static document.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Finalize in eSign Server</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>A feature that allows you to open the envelope inside the Adobe Sign console.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </tbody>
            </tgroup>
         </table>
      </p>
      <p>For more information about terms used with Power products, see <xref href="https://documentation.Power.com/display/CPG/Power+Product+Glossary"
